text: Xylotrechus annobonae is a species of longhorn beetles in the family Cerambycidae. The species is endemic to the island of Annobón in Equatorial Guinea.Tavakilian G. & Chevillotte H. (2018). Base de données Titan sur les Cerambycidés ou Longicornes. Xylotrechus annobonae. Accessed: 21 January 2019 The species was named by Christopher Aurivillius in 1910. ==References== Category:Cerambycidae Category:Endemic fauna of Annobón Category:Invertebrates of Equatorial Guinea Category:Beetles described in 1910
